reviews.title: Nice place and good food
reviews.text: The restaurant is really light and nice, the service is good but the most important thing is the food and it's really good!

reviews.title: Hangout for locals
reviews.text: Great coffee and breakfast and lunch. Large table in the center of the restaurant where you sit and read the newspapers, magazines while enjoying a cup of coffee. Many of the locals come here for breakfast or lunch. You can sit outside as well. Close to a small shopping mall. Friendly staff, you order at the counter and the staff will bring it to your table.

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

articleContent.title: Why Greenville, SC is the perfect mix of adventure and luxury

seoInfo.metaDescription: There are few places that blend luxury and outdoor adventure like Greenville, South Carolina. The days (and mild weather) are made for adrenaline rushes of all types, while the region’s spas, fine dining, and boutique properties serve up luxury experiences that last well into the evening. It’s not hard to dive into a handful of the many treats on offer, and crafting an itinerary that incorporates a little bit of everything is how you’ll find yourself with a Greenville-shaped spot forever in your heart.

articleContent.title: A guide to Newtown: Sydney's coolest neighbourhood

seoInfo.metaDescription: From King Street to Enmore, there's lots to do in this trendy Inner West suburb. Here's our guide to the best restaurants, things to do and hotels in Newtown.

articleContent.title: A food lover’s guide to North Myrtle Beach

seoInfo.metaDescription: Whether it’s shoulder season or summer’s peak, you’ll always find delicious dishes at North Myrtle Beach. Dine by the waterfront after a balmy beach day, eat like the locals at treasured hotspots, or take the family out for a celebratory meal. Whatever you crave in an unforgettable vacation, you’re sure to find it here in this must-read roundup of top restaurants.
Here are more than a dozen places to paddle, cast a line, and raise your mainsail.

tripContent.title: Discover Louisville’s global cuisine at these hidden gems
tripContent.description: When it comes to your taste buds, Louisville’s lively food scene invites you to adventure beyond city limits. Plan your culinary exploration with this roundup of the city’s most-loved eateries, serving classic and creative dishes inspired by food and festivities from around the world.

tripContent.title: Head to Fort Myers for amazing outdoor adventures
tripContent.description: Seeking adventure on your next vacation? Head to the greater Fort Myers area, where action-packed onshore and offshore activities are yours to enjoy year-round. Water sports, nature parks and wildlife excursions are just some of the highlights on this itinerary that is all about having fun in the sun.
